metadata.doc: How can I charge GST on orders? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsPaymentsHow can I charge GST on orders?How can I charge GST on orders?Learn how to set up GST charges for your storeNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoNote: This is applicable only to users in India. To know about setting up taxes for users outside India, click here. To set up GST charges on app, click here to jump to the section. How to set GST charges on WebHead over to the Store settings section by clicking the dropdown on the right side.Head over to the Extra charges section and enable the GST option Add your GST number and the GST percentage. Click on the Save changes button when done. How to set GST charges on App To add additional GST charge on all your orders, click on Manage and then select Extra Charges. Click on the toggle next to GST and turn it on.  Here, enter your GST number and the percentage of GST you wish to charge. metadata.title: How to use Dukaan Credits? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to use Dukaan Credits? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsMarketingHow to use Dukaan Credits?How to use Dukaan Credits?Learn what are Dukaan Credits and how to use themNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoNote: This is applicable only to users in India. Dukaan Credits is a wallet where you can purchase and add credits to manage marketing campaigns and use Dukaan Delivery, seamlessly and hassle-free. Note that 1 Dukaan Credit = Rs. 1. To add Dukaan Credits to your account, click on the Available Credits button at the bottom left. What are the benefits of using Dukaan Credits?Dukaan Credit offers you below benefits to help run your business smoothly:Easy and Quick - It saves you a lot of time when you're setting up marketing campaigns or using Dukaan Delivery. You don't need to enter your card details every time to make the transaction.  How to add Dukaan Credits to my store?To add Dukaan Credits, click on the Available Credits button at the bottom left as shown above. Once clicked, you'll see the below screen. Click on Add Credits button to begin. Now enter the number of credits that you want to purchase. Please note 1 credit = Rs. 1. Here, enter the credits you want to purchase and click on Add Credits button. You can buy credits via UPI, Debit Card, Credit Card, or Netbanking. Once you complete the payment, the credits will be added to your account.   Please note: Dukaan Credits are non-refundable. Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.doc: AreaLandmarkCity PincodeState. Once you've entered the required details, click on Add customer. Upon clicking on Add customer, the customer you have created will be added to your store's customer list. Payment Details:After adding the Products and Customer details, you will be able to view the Payment details.  Here you can also add a coupon code to give an extra discount to the customer. To add a coupon, click on Add Coupon. Upon clicking on Add Coupon, you will need to enter the Coupon Code of the coupon you want to provide.  (Note: The coupon you enter needs to be activated in the discounts section. To learn how to add coupons click here)Payment Methods to create a Manual OrderIn this section, you can choose the mode of payment. There are 2 modes of payment that you can use here, Cash on Delivery (COD) or Prepaid.  If you've chosen COD the payment status will be shown as COD on the order details page. In the case of COD, a confirmation message will also be sent to the customer. If the chosen mode of payment is Prepaid, the payment status will be shown as Paid. Source:Here, you can specify the source of the order. i.e. from where you received the order. To add a source click on the textbox below Source. Click on Create source. Upon clicking on Create source, you will be able to add a new source from where you received the order. (Note: By default, no source will be selected.  After you've entered all the details you can click on Create order. metadata.title: How to enable online payments on Mobile? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to enable online payments on Mobile? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsPaymentsHow to enable online payments on Mobile?How to enable online payments on Mobile?NWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoTo enable online payments for your store go to the Manage section, click on Online Payments and then verify your UPI ID or Bank Account. Once verified, you can now accept online payments on your store. You can also set custom payment methods like:1. Cash on Delivery - Your store will only accept Cash on Delivery orders.2. Online Payments - Your store will only accept online payments via UPI/Debit/Credit Cards or Net Banking.3. Both Options (Recommended) - You will be able to accept payments via Cash on Delivery or UPI/Debit/Credit Cards or Netbanking. Transaction Charges:We charge the following processing fees on online transactions. Also, the maximum transaction charges are capped to Rs. 150 per transaction. This means that you won't be paying more than Rs. 150 on transaction charges if the order amount is big.PlanOnline Payments Transaction ChargesGold1.49%Silver2.99%Read this to know how to set up online payments and complete KYC to increase the transaction limit on online payments. If you have any questions regarding the payments, get in touch with us at support@mydukaan.io now.Read MoreHow to use online payments for your store?How to do KYC to increase the payment limit?How to use the payment link to accept online payment on COD orders? metadata.title: What should I do if I do not want to receive orders on a particular day? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: What should I do if I do not want to receive orders on a particular day? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsStore ProfileWhat should I do if I do not want to receive orders on a particular day?What should I do if I do not want to receive orders on a particular day?Learn how to switch your store Offline or OnlineNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoJust like physical stores are closed at the end of the day or not opened due to any reason, you can also switch your Dukaan store Offline or Online as per your convenience. To turn your store Offline, Click on the toggle button at the top right which says Online. Choose the option when you want your store to be Online again. Your store will automatically be Online, once the selected time frame is over. Once your store is online, your customers can again place the orders. Only if you choose I’ll go online myself option, you have to manually switch your store to Online, whenever you want to. Click Confirm and your store will be Offline.  To switch your store online at any time, click on the toggle that says Offline at the top right to turn it back to Online.
